---
import Layout from '@/components/chrome/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-05-07';
---
<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — strguests.tools"
  description="How strguests.tools handles your data: what we collect, what we don't, and how to reach us with questions."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-12 prose">
    <header>
      <p class="label text-[color:var(--accent-700)]">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="mt-2 font-serif text-h1 text-navy">
        Privacy Policy<span class="period-accent">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-small text-ink-3 font-mono">Last updated <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{lastUpdated}</time></p>
    </header>

    <section class="mt-9">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">What we collect</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ui text-graphite leading-relaxed">
        strguests.tools is a static, browser-side site. Most of what you do here never leaves your
        device — the PDF generators run entirely in your browser, and the form fields you fill in
        are not transmitted to us.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ui text-graphite leading-relaxed">
        We collect data in three narrow situations:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-3 ml-6 list-disc text-ui text-graphite space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Email captures.</strong> If you submit your email through one of our forms (lead
          magnet, waitlist), we store it with a tag identifying which form, then send it to our
          email service provider so we can email you the requested resource.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics.</strong> We use Google Analytics 4 to count page views and basic
          interactions (which generator was used, whether a PDF was downloaded). GA4 sets cookies
          and may collect IP address, user-agent, and referrer. No personally identifiable info is
          sent to GA4 by us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Server logs.</strong> Our hosting provider logs requests (timestamp, path,
          status code, IP) for security and diagnostics. These logs rotate and are not used for
          marketing.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-9">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">What we don't do</h2>
      <ul class="mt-3 ml-6 list-disc text-ui text-graphite space-y-2">
        <li>We don't sell your data.</li>
        <li>We don't share your email with third parties (other than the email service provider that delivers it).</li>
        <li>We don't run ads, retargeting pixels, or session-replay tools.</li>
        <li>We don't store the content you type into the generator forms — that stays in your browser.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-9">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Your choices</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ui text-graphite leading-relaxed">
        Most browsers let you block analytics cookies via their "Do Not Track" or extension
        settings. If you've ever subscribed and want off the list, every email we send has an
        unsubscribe link, or you can email us directly (below).
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ui text-graphite leading-relaxed">
        If you're in the EU, UK, or California and want a copy or deletion of any data we hold,
        email <a class="text-[color:var(--accent-700)]" href="mailto:hello@strguests.tools">hello@strguests.tools</a>
        and we'll handle it within 30 days.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-9">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-h2 text-navy">Contact</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-ui text-graphite leading-relaxed">
        Questions about this policy? Email <a class="text-[color:var(--accent-700)]" href="mailto:hello@strguests.tools">hello@strguests.tools</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
